currently topi.split takes `indices_or_sections` as splitting argument. 

@tqchen  I need clarification if this operator is fully compatible with numpy: https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy-1.15.1/reference/generated/numpy.split.html or not.
More specifically, what is the behavior if integer N is used to split the array, but cannot be evenly divided? Numpy says `If indices_or_sections is an integer, N, the array will be divided into N equal arrays along axis. If such a split is not possible, an error is raised.` However, we can use `np.array_split` in such cases.

